# Design: Fix squash-merge release finalization

## Architecture

Single-function change in `resolveReleaseReachability` (`git-finalize.ts:1702-1728`). No new types, no new interfaces, no new functions. Adds a fallback branch after the existing direct-route ancestry check.

## Current flow (direct route)

```
route === "direct"
  → verifyDefaultBranchPushed → if not pushed → origin_push_unverified
  → verifyChangeBranchReachableFromOrigin → if reachable → origin_default
  → if not reachable → origin_unmerged (FAILS HERE for squash merges)
```

## New flow (direct route)

```
route === "direct"
  → verifyDefaultBranchPushed → if not pushed → origin_push_unverified
  → verifyChangeBranchReachableFromOrigin → if reachable → origin_default
  → if not reachable:
      → if prNumber && route.repo:
          → readPrMergeState(mainCheckout, route.repo, prNumber, deps)
          → if MERGED + mergedAt → pr_merged (NEW FALLBACK)
          → else → origin_unmerged (unchanged)
      → else → origin_unmerged (unchanged)
```

## Implementation detail

In `resolveReleaseReachability`, replace lines 1721-1727:

```typescript
// BEFORE:
return originReachability.reachable
  ? { reachable: true, proof: "origin_default" }
  : {
      reachable: false,
      proof: "origin_unmerged",
      details: originReachability.unmergedCommits,
    };

// AFTER:
if (originReachability.reachable) {
  return { reachable: true, proof: "origin_default" };
}

// Squash-merge fallback: check PR state when ancestry fails
if (input.prNumber && route.repo) {
  const prState = readPrMergeState(
    input.mainCheckout,
    route.repo,
    input.prNumber,
    deps,
  );
  if (!("error" in prState) && prState.state === "MERGED" && prState.mergedAt) {
    return {
      reachable: true,
      proof: "pr_merged",
      prNumber: input.prNumber,
      mergeCommitOid: prState.mergeCommitOid,
    };
  }
}

return {
  reachable: false,
  proof: "origin_unmerged",
  details: originReachability.unmergedCommits,
};
```

## LBP decisions

| Decision | Chosen | Rejected | Why |
|---|---|---|---|
| Where to add fallback | Inside `resolveReleaseReachability` | In `getReleaseFinalizationBlocker` (gate.ts) | Keeps reachability logic co-located; gate.ts already delegates to this function |
| How to detect squash merge | PR merge state via `readPrMergeState` | `git log --grep` or commit message parsing | PR state is authoritative; git log parsing is fragile |
| When to trigger fallback | Only when ancestry fails + prNumber + repo available | Always check PR state for direct route | Avoids unnecessary `gh` calls on happy path |
| Proof type | Reuse `"pr_merged"` | New `"squash_merged"` proof | Existing proof already covers PR-merged-via-any-method; gate.ts handles it correctly |

## Test strategy

4 new tests in `git-finalize.test.ts`:
1. Direct route + squash-merged PR → `reachable: true, proof: "pr_merged"`
2. Direct route + no prNumber → `origin_unmerged` (no fallback attempted)
3. Direct route + prNumber but PR not merged → `origin_unmerged`
4. Direct route + prNumber but `gh` fails → `origin_unmerged`

1 new integration test in `gate.release-enforcement.test.ts`:
5. Release gate allows completion when direct route ancestry fails but PR is squash-merged
